1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,877
[mysterious theme music playing]

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:07,882
[Manuel, in English] This is going to be
the best day of my life!

3
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:10,468
[Konno, in English] We are
very pleased to be here for this summit.

4
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:12,846
[Manuel, in English]
<i>This is Task Force Alpha.</i>

5
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:16,349
[in English] <i>They will</i>
<i>personally be in charge</i>

6
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:19,561
<i>of your security and protection</i>
<i>for the whole day.</i>

7
00:00:19,644 --> 00:00:23,648
What scheme are you
cooking up now, General Carillo?

8
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:27,694
[reporter] <i>The summit has officially begun</i>
<i>for a major investment deal</i>

9
00:00:27,777 --> 00:00:31,239
<i>between Japanese investors</i>
<i>and Filipino businessmen.</i>

10
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:34,367
[Espina] <i>I still don't know</i>
<i>what General Carillo is planning.</i>

11
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,161
Let's just keep watching him.

12
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:38,496
Welcome back to the service!

13
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:41,166
[Manuel] <i>I hope you've come</i>
<i>to your senses, young man.</i>

14
00:00:41,249 --> 00:00:42,792
[Marcus] <i>I'm a lot more cautious now.</i>

15
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:47,088
[Manuel] <i>As you should. Don't make</i>
<i>the same mistake twice.</i>

16
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:49,007
[Marcus] <i>I think General Carillo</i>
<i>is planning something.</i>

17
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:51,342
Espina and I think
he's going to do it here.

18
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:52,594
Why would he do it here?

19
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:54,220
[Azuelo] <i>To create destabilization?</i>

20
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,765
<i>What for? So he could seize power?</i>

21
00:00:56,848 --> 00:00:59,726
<i>Just drop it, Agent Reyes. Goddammit.</i>

22
00:01:00,518 --> 00:01:02,353
[Esina] <i>Are you working</i>
<i>with General Carillo?</i>

23
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:05,148
<i>If you are, what kind of chaos</i>
<i>are you planning?</i>

24
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:07,776
[man] <i>It's begun.</i>

25
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,652
[tense music playing]

26
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,154
[overlapping dialogue]

27
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:12,572
Sit down! Now!

28
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:13,782
[cries, shrieks]

29
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:16,159
[in Japanese] From now on,
you are our hostages!

30
00:01:16,242 --> 00:01:17,911
- [gunshots blasting]
- [grunts]

31
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:18,995
[delegate in Japanese] What's happening?

32
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:20,663
- [man 1, in English] What's wrong?
- [man 2] Oh…

33
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:22,582
‪[dramatic sting]

34
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,001
[in English] That's my wife
and my daughter!

35
00:01:25,084 --> 00:01:27,462
[Azuelo] <i>Agent Reyes's hunch was right!</i>

36
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:30,924
[Marcus, in English] <i>All units,</i>
<i>gather at the main exit point.</i>

37
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:32,383
[in English] <i>We move out in two minutes.</i>

38
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:44,395
[mysterious theme music playing]

39
00:01:55,532 --> 00:01:58,243
- [tense music playing]
- Agent Angeles,

40
00:01:58,326 --> 00:02:01,871
give me the coordinates
of San Aurelio Street.

41
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:03,414
[in English] Sending you the coordinates.

42
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:06,751
[in English] Um, we're… we're preparing
the digital perimeter right now.

43
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:10,380
[tense music playing]

44
00:02:19,889 --> 00:02:20,932
[in English] Let's move!

45
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:40,952
[in English] Everyone! Calm down!

46
00:02:41,035 --> 00:02:44,581
[in English] Task Force Alpha
is an elite team!

47
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,208
[in English] They can handle everything!

48
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:49,919
Yulo and Valdez's arrest

49
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,504
isn't the end of it all.

50
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:54,716
That's what Major Espina thinks, too.

51
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:58,344
We think those two are just fall guys.

52
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:00,763
What do you mean?

53
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:04,434
Sir, it's possible that this
is part of a larger plan

54
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:06,769
to divert us from the truth.

55
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,479
Why?

56
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:10,815
Who do you think is responsible for this?

57
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:13,359
Do you even have a lead?

58
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:16,446
General Carillo, sir.

59
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:19,282
[dramatic sting]

60
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:20,325
‪[camera shutters clicking]

61
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:23,202
[all talking frantically]

62
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,038
- [in English] No! I'll go!
- [in English] They'll be fine.

63
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:30,251
[in Japanese] That's my family.
I can't just sit here and watch.

64
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:33,338
[in English] They'll be fine,
Mr. Konno. Mr. Konno!

65
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:41,221
[pensive music playing]

66
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,097
‪[thuds]

67
00:03:48,811 --> 00:03:50,521
- [intense music playing]
- [police sirens blaring]

68
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:52,190
POLICE

69
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:29,394
[Candy] What's going on?

70
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:31,437
- [man] Sir, that's forbidden.
- [Candy] Excuse me.

71
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:34,232
We are currently at San Aurelio Street

72
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:37,694
where a hostage-taking crisis
is taking place.

73
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:41,531
So far, the information we have
is that this bus

74
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,408
- is full of Japanese tourists.
- [dramatic sting]

75
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:46,327
The hostage-takers' identity and demands

76
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,537
are yet to be found out.

77
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,748
Present here as well is Task Force Alpha,

78
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:52,500
- [man groans]
- who just successfully handled

79
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:55,169
a school shooting incident recently.

80
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:56,504
So we are hoping

81
00:04:56,587 --> 00:04:58,840
that they resolve
this one properly as well.

82
00:04:58,923 --> 00:05:01,175
[dramatic sting]

83
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:07,598
[grim music playing]

84
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:16,816
Goodness. There goes our luck.

85
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:18,568
This is dangerous.

86
00:05:18,651 --> 00:05:20,570
A lot of innocent people might die again.

87
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:24,615
The Japanese will definitely
lose trust in us.

88
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:26,951
And what would happen to the investments

89
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,494
we're looking forward to?

90
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,121
- [woman] Yeah.
- [man] That's right.

91
00:05:30,204 --> 00:05:32,874
That's another job opportunity
thrown out the window.

92
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:40,298
[tense music playing]

93
00:05:40,381 --> 00:05:42,675
Sir. Sir, wait. You can't…

94
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,802
- [Konno, in Japanese] Let go of me!
- Sir…

95
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,220
- [Konno] My family is in there!
- We're taking care of the situation.

96
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:47,764
[in Japanese] I have to save them!

97
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:49,807
- [in Japanese] I have to save my family!
- [Felix, indistinct]

98
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,517
‪-[in Japanese] I have to save them!
‪-[Felix, in English] Wait, sir.

99
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:53,311
- [Konno whimpers]
- [Felix, in English] Stay calm.

100
00:05:53,394 --> 00:05:54,228
[in English] Stay calm!

101
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:56,314
[crying, in Japanese] My family…

102
00:05:56,397 --> 00:05:58,858
Miss Suher! Miss Suher!

103
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:00,610
Have you seen this?

104
00:06:00,693 --> 00:06:03,780
The TFA is rescuing
some Japanese hostages.

105
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:07,533
Oh, dear. What's going on?

106
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:09,911
What are they doing there?

107
00:06:09,994 --> 00:06:12,955
Aren't they supposed to be
at the investment summit?

108
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,208
It's Usman!

109
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,252
It's my son.

110
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,505
Why is he there?

111
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:24,467
‪[digital trilling]

112
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:28,888
[in English] Um… Marcus, we've…
we've identified the suspects. Um…

113
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:31,724
[Lara, in English] <i>Their names</i>
<i>are Lydia and Benny Santerva.</i>

114
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:33,392
[in English] Both in their forties.

115
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:35,144
Um, according to the records,

116
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:39,107
they're both employees
of Lakbay-Ngiti Travel & Tours.

117
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,650
What are their motives?

118
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:44,278
Why are they holding
their clients hostage?

119
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:46,656
[in English] We're…
We're still looking into it.

120
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:47,573
[radio static]

121
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:03,131
Do you think they're working for Carillo?

122
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,346
- Secure the perimeter.
- [agent] Yes, sir.

123
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,021
[megaphone screeches]

124
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:25,653
Benny and Lydia Santerva.

125
00:07:26,362 --> 00:07:30,158
I am Agent Marcus Reyes
of Task Force Alpha.

126
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:32,743
We know who you are.

127
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,079
We have also surrounded the bus.

128
00:07:35,163 --> 00:07:36,372
‪[intense dramatic music playing]

129
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:45,298
Nobody has to get hurt.

130
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,636
We can talk about this properly.

131
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,306
Tell me what you need.

132
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:55,933
[hostages whimpering, crying]

133
00:07:57,852 --> 00:08:00,062
- You! Stand up!
- [screaming]

134
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:05,985
If anyone moves, I'm going to shoot her!

135
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:07,820
Do you understand?

136
00:08:10,448 --> 00:08:11,949
[hostages crying, begging]

137
00:08:14,368 --> 00:08:15,203
Lydia…

138
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:17,830
- Come here!
- Move!

139
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:21,918
- What's that?!
- [crying]

140
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,382
[sobbing]

141
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,592
Listen up, cops!

142
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:33,429
Don't come closer, or we'll kill them all!

143
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,140
Sir.

144
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:39,101
The suspect is speaking through
Mr. Konno's daughter's live.

145
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:43,731
<i>Wanna know why we're doing this?</i>

146
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:45,149
<i>We do this for the country!</i>

147
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:47,860
[Benny] Because of that
goddamn investment deal,

148
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:51,405
the government can make fools out of us!

149
00:08:51,989 --> 00:08:54,492
And with that goddamn investment deal,

150
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:57,078
they can sell our sovereignty!

151
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:02,041
<i>They're promising us temporary jobs</i>

152
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,962
<i>for a lifetime's worth of slavery!</i>

153
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:08,965
<i>They're going to take advantage of us,</i>

154
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:12,385
<i>those capitalist foreigners!</i>

155
00:09:12,468 --> 00:09:16,264
<i>They're taking advantage</i>
<i>of the working class!</i>

156
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:20,184
<i>So we call to stop that investment deal</i>

157
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,603
<i>with those imperialist foreigners!</i>

158
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:25,982
<i>Destroy imperialism!</i>

159
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:28,109
‪-[dramatic sting]
‪-[music intensifies]

160
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:32,363
‪[dramatic sting]

161
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:54,427
<i>Let's go back</i>
<i>to the ongoing hostage-taking</i>

162
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:56,137
<i>at San Aurelio Street.</i>

163
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,889
<i>Candy, have the suspects been identified?</i>

164
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:02,727
According to the information
handed to us by the authorities,

165
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:05,271
the two suspects are husband and wife,

166
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:08,232
Benny and Lydia Santerva.

167
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,735
Wait, I know those people.

168
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:13,070
They're one of my regular customers here.

169
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:14,238
Really?

170
00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:16,991
That means, you always
got to interact with them.

171
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:18,034
How scary.

172
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:21,787
It is reported that this couple
has been involved

173
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:24,415
in the activist movement
since their college days.

174
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:26,500
According to authorities,

175
00:10:26,584 --> 00:10:31,297
Benny and Lydia held
the Japanese tourists hostage

176
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,758
as protest to the ongoing

177
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:36,344
Japan-Philippines Investment Summit.

178
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:41,140
You know, Benny and Lydia are good people.

179
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:44,185
Even their daughter, Jennie.

180
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:47,313
I remember the other day,

181
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:51,859
they came here crying
because their daughter is missing.

182
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:54,195
Oh, dear.

183
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,238
How did it get this bad?

184
00:10:56,322 --> 00:11:00,076
<i>Now, let's move on to an interview</i>
<i>with General Carillo.</i>

185
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,954
General Carillo,
what is your official assessment

186
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:07,249
on the suspects' statement
on their live stream?

187
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,378
[in English] This is definitely
a terrorist attack.

188
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:12,004
[in English] Let us not sugarcoat it.

189
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:17,385
Those people are like terrorist cells

190
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:21,639
who have been observing
our security for a long time.

191
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:25,226
They have access to high-powered firearms

192
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:28,604
because they are so easy
to buy on the black market.

193
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:31,982
Should the government be blamed
for the incident

194
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:34,777
because of the lack of control
over the arms trade?

195
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:39,907
[sighs] The government is doing
everything in its power

196
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:44,537
to combat the problem
with illegal firearms.

197
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:48,707
But because of syndicate protectors,

198
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:55,297
it has been difficult
to eliminate this problem.

199
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:59,301
[scoffs] So even leftists,
like that couple,

200
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,805
have access to those guns. [scoffs]

201
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:05,808
And now they are using them
to create chaos.

202
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:10,312
[in English] But, uh,
let's not blame the government.

203
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:16,277
This is not the time
for us to blame each other.

204
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:22,032
Now is the time for us
to unite against terrorism.

205
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:25,119
[in English] Trust our men on the ground.

206
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:28,956
[in English] Task Force Alpha
is handling it.

207
00:12:29,457 --> 00:12:31,500
[tense music playing]

208
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:36,714
No matter what you're fighting for,

209
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:39,884
don't hurt innocent people.

210
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:42,219
Let the tourists go!

211
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:45,181
<i>Get the Japanese out of our country first!</i>

212
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,182
MY GOD, PLEASE
I HOPE NO CIVILIANS ARE INVOLVED

213
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,099
I HOPE THIS ENDS PEACEFULLY

214
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:50,060
Then we'll let everyone here go!

215
00:12:53,022 --> 00:12:56,066
It's not that simple, Benny, Lydia.

216
00:12:57,151 --> 00:13:00,279
Hand over the hostages safely first,

217
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:04,408
and I'll make sure your demands

218
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:08,370
reach the highest authorities.

219
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:10,539
<i>Didn't you hear us?!</i>

220
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,125
<i>Do what we say first!</i>

221
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:17,838
[Marcus] Fine.

222
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:19,924
But there's a wounded person inside.

223
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:26,013
Let us send someone to treat him.

224
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:29,058
I'll give you a few minutes to decide.

225
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:34,271
I'll call the phone you're holding soon.

226
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,733
[sobbing, sniffling]

227
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:43,364
[in English] Let's move back.

228
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:52,164
[Marcus] We can't just enter
the bus recklessly.

229
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:54,708
[Marcus] <i>They might kill the hostages.</i>

230
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:58,796
I'll negotiate so one of us can enter

231
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:00,256
to neutralize the targets.

232
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:05,302
I'll do it.

233
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,388
I'll go in.

234
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:10,766
Alright.

235
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:15,938
Sabdani, Domingo, secure the perimeter.

236
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,898
Make sure no one comes near us.

237
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,191
[in English] Yes, sir.

238
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:21,151
[in English] The rest of the team…

239
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:23,279
Keep an eye out for the hostages.

240
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:25,030
You are the ones who will save them.

241
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:27,867
We will wait for Espina's go signal.

242
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,285
[in English] Clear?

243
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:30,244
[in English] Clear!

244
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:33,998
[Konno sniffles]

245
00:14:35,499 --> 00:14:40,921
[in English] You can call
my daughter's cellphone.

246
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:43,632
[Konno sobbing]

247
00:14:45,509 --> 00:14:47,261
[in English] Save my daughter and wife!

248
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:52,057
- [sobbing]
- [gasps]

249
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,518
- [in English] Please…
- [Marcus, in English] Yes, sir.

250
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:55,853
[in Japanese] It's your dad… [sniffles]

251
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:00,941
[sobbing, in Japanese] Please save us…

252
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,735
[Marcus exhales heavily]

253
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:05,070
[Marcus, in English] Thank you.

254
00:15:07,114 --> 00:15:11,785
- [tense music playing]
- [gasps]

255
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:18,542
Hon, what do we do?

256
00:15:19,209 --> 00:15:20,127
Hon…

257
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:25,633
It's almost two o'clock.

258
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:29,219
[clock beeping]

259
00:15:29,303 --> 00:15:31,931
They said they'll release Jennie,

260
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:34,558
then we can release the hostages.

261
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:38,437
This will be over soon.

262
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:42,566
[dramatic stinging]

263
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:47,947
Those terrorists are just
creating a diversion

264
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:51,533
- to distract us from the real threat!
- [woman shouts]

265
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:55,287
They must've planted a bomb here too!

266
00:15:55,371 --> 00:15:57,456
[people clamoring]

267
00:15:57,539 --> 00:15:58,457
[man] Men!

268
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:00,834
[in English] Men, this is Command!

269
00:16:01,627 --> 00:16:03,879
[in English] Initiate a full-grid sweep
of the area now!

270
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,799
- [dramatic sting]
- [timer beeping]

271
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:07,716
‪[dramatic stinging]

272
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:10,386
‪-[dramatic sting]
‪-[beeping]

273
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:14,640
[suspenseful music playing]

274
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,559
PHILJAPAN
MIRAIKONA ECONOMIC SUMMIT

275
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:21,146
[line ringing]

276
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:22,773
You know what to do with the child.

277
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,233
Yes, sir.

278
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:29,071
[Jennie crying]

279
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:41,834
I don't want to die.

280
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:45,671
We can't die here.

281
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:48,215
What will happen to Jennie if we die?

282
00:16:48,799 --> 00:16:51,343
We're not going to die. Okay?

283
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:55,973
- It's almost two o'clock.
- [sobbing]

284
00:16:56,056 --> 00:16:58,559
We're doing this for her.

285
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:02,062
We can save her. Then, we can surrender.

286
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,731
Hang in there.

287
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,442
Okay?

288
00:17:09,194 --> 00:17:10,821
[in English] You're not terrorists?

289
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:14,658
[in English] So you're not planning
to kill us?

290
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:26,295
[in English] Is someone
forcing you to do this?

291
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:30,257
[in English] Because Jennie was kidnapped?

292
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,218
[in English] Yes.

293
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,555
[in English] Jennie's our daughter.

294
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:51,195
[in Japanese]
They don't intend to kill us.

295
00:17:51,779 --> 00:17:58,285
[in Japanese] They're doing this

296
00:17:58,368 --> 00:18:03,916
because someone kidnapped
their daughter, Jennie.

297
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:10,839
[in Japanese] They have to do this
in order to save her.

298
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:13,509
[grim music playing]

299
00:18:27,898 --> 00:18:29,983
[sobs]

300
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:33,445
[in Japanese] Even though it's hard,

301
00:18:33,529 --> 00:18:36,573
I understand you.

302
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:40,035
[in Japanese] I would do anything

303
00:18:40,619 --> 00:18:43,997
for my daughter too.

304
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:49,211
[in Japanese] I hope your daughter

305
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:52,673
is safe.

306
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:55,551
[Lydia sobbing]

307
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:08,105
[sobbing continues]

308
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,904
[Sean, in English] Command, I have
a green light on Subject Alpha.

309
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,990
- [in English] And I have a clear shot.
- [radio static]

310
00:19:18,949 --> 00:19:21,326
[in English] Sighting confirmed
on Subject Bravo.

311
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:22,578
- [in English] I'm on her.
- [radio static]

312
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:23,704
[Marcus, in English] Negative.

313
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:25,414
[in English] Hold your fire.

314
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:27,624
[Marcus, in English] <i>Stand by.</i>

315
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:30,043
We don't want bloodshed.

316
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:30,961
‪[digital trilling]

317
00:19:32,796 --> 00:19:34,590
- We will wait for their response.
- [radio static]

318
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:37,926
[suspenseful music playing]

319
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:45,392
Sir!

320
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:48,604
Negative on secondary devices.
No visible bomb.

321
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:55,485
- [tense ominous music playing]
- [timer beeping]

322
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:05,954
‪-[dramatic sting]
‪-[tense music playing]

323
00:20:12,794 --> 00:20:13,629
‪[rhythmic thudding]

324
00:20:15,631 --> 00:20:19,968
- [pensive music playing]
- [breathing shakily]

325
00:20:31,647 --> 00:20:33,523
[in English] I-Is this what I think it is?

326
00:20:33,607 --> 00:20:39,529
[in English] At exactly
1:45 p.m. tomorrow,

327
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:43,533
you will have to press that button.

328
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:45,827
[in English] Dad…

329
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:50,123
A lot of innocent people will die.
People with families, Dad.

330
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:54,586
We've talked about this many times, Lara!

331
00:20:55,170 --> 00:21:01,134
[in English] You make sacrifices
for the greater good!

332
00:21:01,885 --> 00:21:07,140
[in English] Lara,
victory is within our reach.

333
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:13,480
I am placing in your hands the decision

334
00:21:14,147 --> 00:21:17,567
whether we succeed or not.

335
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:19,611
Why me?

336
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:21,697
Why me?

337
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:30,622
[in English] Because I want
to know if you…

338
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:37,296
are still the daughter that I raised.

339
00:21:37,379 --> 00:21:39,589
[sobs, sighs]

340
00:21:40,507 --> 00:21:43,176
[morose music playing]

341
00:21:59,818 --> 00:22:01,320
[music turns ominous]

342
00:22:25,343 --> 00:22:29,556
[in English] At 2 p.m., the kidnappers
will release our daughter.

343
00:22:29,639 --> 00:22:31,016
- [Lydia] <i>This will all be over.</i>
- [tense music playing]

344
00:22:31,099 --> 00:22:33,852
[Azuelo] If Carillo's behind all this,

345
00:22:33,935 --> 00:22:35,020
who are his accomplices?

346
00:22:35,103 --> 00:22:37,064
This is not the method
your brother would've wanted.

347
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:38,857
Who are you to say that?

348
00:22:38,940 --> 00:22:41,526
[Manuel] <i>What matters more to me?</i>

349
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:44,696
Family or country?

350
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:48,241
[Manuel, in English] <i>At exactly 1:45 p.m.,</i>

351
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:51,244
- <i>you will have to press that button.</i>
- [sobbing]

352
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,538
[in English] I'm sorry… I'm sorry, Dad…

353
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:57,375
[Felix] Madam! What's happening to you?!

354
00:22:57,459 --> 00:22:59,044
- Madam!
- [sobbing]

355
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:01,338
I will send someone in.

356
00:23:01,421 --> 00:23:03,590
[Marcus] <i>He will only treat</i>
<i>the injured person there.</i>

357
00:23:03,673 --> 00:23:06,218
- Alright, we agree.
- [man] <i>Alright.</i>

358
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:11,014
Lara… what are you doing?

359
00:23:11,098 --> 00:23:12,057
- [Felix] Madam!
- [Lara sobbing]

360
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,977
[Lara sobbing, breathing shakily]

361
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,356
[timer beeping]
